<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Delheru on 10-13-2000 09:26 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Heh frankly I'd have done just like the cleric the original rant is about. I don't like wasting my time doing stuff like grinding. The simple fact is I don't enjoy camping lame disco or chef in Sebilis. When we're there I want 100% efficiency so I don't have to come back often. This was also very much true pre-RoK.

Ok first of all I'd never join a group which has a cleric already, talk about bad efficiency unless there are undead against you (even then its quite few levels when clerics actually are decent damage). 
I totally refuse to watch cleric/shaman/druid melee though. If they do I tell them to stop. Only exception to the rule is shaman atm with the FA. And after they proc their ass should be on the ground too  ;)

Of course this depends on how you play. I play to achieve stuff, to do stuff more efficiently than anyone else, with less people etc. Of course I strike sparks with less powergaming people, since I will not tolerate silly timeconsuming behaviour which is wasting like 3-5% of our damage potential (ie medding & nuking vs melee from a cleric). If I have to grind 100h (which I'm sure I will), you have just wasted 3-5h of my damage theoretically. So hell yes I intervene every time I see someone doing something silly :P

This is one of the reasons I usually only group with the people I know though  ;)

-- Delheru Tanreall
